76561198025301599,Recommended,314220,17175762,"Posted: 22 July, 2015",all,ZOR33L is,"A bomberman clone to the bones, which is great news for me as i really love Bomberman games since i was a child. this game has the exact same gameplay, from the commentary when collecting power-ups to the stage hazards and even the power-ups are the same from the bomberman games. (1-5 players can play locally)and in case you don't know what Bomberman is. the game main objective is to kill your enemies with the blast from your bomb. the camera is as you see from the screenshots is top-down view, the maps has randomly generated blocks patterns. you start with a weak bomb and you use it to break the blocks and collect power-ups like (longer blast radius, ability to place more than 1 bomb at a time, ability to throw your bomb or push it...etc.if you have friends to play with then this game is a blast to play for sure."
,Recommended,314220,22542973,"Posted: 20 April, 2016",all,Silver Nova,"All right. Lets get the big thing out of the way. This game blatantly copies the Bomberman series. Like REALLY blatantly. Even the icon designs look like they were taken directly from the titles. As such, you'll be seeing a lot of comparisons between this game and that series in this review.The game is rather challenging and will be quick to ramp up the challenge from level to level, even early on. Unlike some games which will give you a small taste of a new trap or enemy before throwing them at you in full force, this game takes a trial by fire mentality. Those looking for a challenge will probably like what this game has to offer, just be prepared to adapt quick. Sadly, stages also tend to lack much variety from one another so the single player mode does get repetitive.Aesthetically the game doesn't quite have the charm of the series that inspired it. The music is all taken from public domain and mostly seems rather understated. One problem that arises from the aesthetics is the playable character's design. Due to his bulkiness, it becomes difficult to tell if he is safely hidden from an explosion or still in the line of fire. Multiple self destructs have resulted from me trying to determine the character's hitbox.Of course, given the inspiration, the game has a multiplayer battle mode. and if you liked it in Bomberman than you're in luck because it's literally an exact copy of everything from those games, from the level designs, to the power-ups to the stage gimmicks.Overall it's a decent game. Not as good as the series it's clearly trying to be, but given the state of the Bomberman franchise ever since Konami bought it, this is probably the closest to a sequel we're getting for a long while."
