76561198006707000,Recommended,314220,13348195,"Posted: 13 December, 2014",all,Krane,"Miss Bomberman? Get this game!This is a simple, well done tribute to the classic bomberman games.The 'story' mode in this game is challenging to say the least, enemies can avoid bombs, shoot you and break blocks to name a few. There are also environmental hazards to deal with to make things interesting. Both normal levels and bosses have had me rage quit because of how difficult it can be (I'm also terrible so it's not down to bad game design) but I was soon opening the game back up to try again.But for the reason I personally bought it for, multiplayer, it's a great game to just chill out to with a bunch of friends on skype or such like, trash talk them all before screwing up and trapping yourself with your own bomb, classic fun!If you want a low cost bomberman experience you can waste time on and/or play with friends, get this game, you can go one day without a Maccy meal."
76561197985072747,Recommended,314220,13287828,"Posted: 8 December, 2014",all,FantasyFreak_UK,"Genre - Puzzle/Action Blow 'em upThis is not Bomberman, but it plays like Bomberman and an ancient game called Penguin Towers on the C64 (Google it), You have standard battle modes, where you blow up the other players. There is also a single player adventure mode, where you blow up tricky monsters and bosses, which actually seems quite fun. There are various power ups to collect like the throwing glove etc. My favourite version of Bomberman was on the Sega Saturn and this isn't as good as that, but it is better than some of the Bombeman games out there and for a fair price."
